==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supernal
<hw>Su*per"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>supernus</ets>, from <ets>super</ets> above: cf. F.
<ets>supernel</ets>. See <er>Super-</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Being
in a higher place or region; locally higher; <as>as, the
<ex>supernal</ex> orbs; <ex>supernal</ex> regions</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧That <xex>supernal</xex> judge.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Relating or belonging to things above; celestial;
heavenly; <as>as, <ex>supernal</ex> grace</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not by the sufferance of <qex>supernal</qex> power.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supernatant</ent>⟦br⟧
